Yes, the seven, yes, they - they all lived. No, no wasn't the seven - seven youngest ones. It was two - the two elder ones, my - my sister - one of my - my eldest sister and my eldest brother and - that was - John, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12395442\charrsid2754318 Margaret}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12395442\charrsid2754318 Christine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
, Josephine and myself. That's the - was the - was four girls and one boy there then there was Robert and Andrew, see. But - I was the youngest out of the lot. I'm the youngest out of the lot. I was the baby you see of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 You may not remember this but don't worry if you can't?
