was thirty-three. I was old enough to - to know and understand her and look after - we used to - 'course then we lived in Argyll Road when she died. Because she lived next door. She had a place next door, upstairs you see and she was thirty-three when she
 died. That was in 1911.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 She was the third daughter?
