er used to - like - go to - if there was any - them days there used to be ladies with - with - you know, bundles of clothes and that standing at the bottom of the turning and that you see, well - she'd go - if she had any coppers she'd go up there and see
 if there's anything - worth having. She'd bring it home and wash it and she'd make us little dresses or things with it you see. Cut them down and make little things with it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 You said she sometimes used to go out and look for rags and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Oh - well she - if she never had any soap or soda or anything - any money, she used to go out and pick up rags and bring 'em home and wash 'em and dry 'em and take 'em to the - you know, rag people see, well she'd get a couple of coppers for them well
 then she'd get over the soap or soda and do - rub all out - you know, rub all our clothes for us and - have 'em dried and ironed and she put them on next morning. If they - if they came home from school at night and she thought they was a bit grubby well
 that's what she used to do. Put us to bed - wash us and put us to bed and then she'd go out and get these - you know - that's what I say there's nobody can say we was ever left dirty, not - nobody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 She had very high standards?
