Oh yes. No, no. Only - only rabbits and - and - and chickens. Mother kept chickens, yes. She did. In her garden where we lived in Butchers Road. Yes. And she used to get the eggs off a lady in the - in the shop at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10642985\charrsid2754318 corner}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
 - ordinary eggs and she'd - put 'em under a hen and she'd have a - if she laid - put eleven she'd have about nine or she'd put seven she'd hav
e about five, something like that. She was very, very - very wonderful and she'd sit hours - out in that garden talking to them - birds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Encouraging them to lay?
