\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Do you r
emember seeing your mother having less food so the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Oh yes, she often went without, our mother - very often. So that they - if there was any bread left and that she'd leave us all that. Always be a martyr - or a bit of jam or a
nything like that. She wouldn't - she'd make out that she - she'd have a cup of tea and she said, well I'm going to do so and so, - you see, well - if she went to work she might have a - a bit at work you see - a bit of bread and butter or whatever they g
ave her. And they might - some ladies was kind to her and they might have given her a dinner you see. So therefore that's how she used to - manage you see. And then when she got the half a crown she'd bring home the - what she could you see. Out of that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Did your father have more?
