 then she was in - this - place called Brownlow Hill - workhouse you see with the three children. Well then her sister was out - she was married, she used to go and see her and she'd never tell her when her husband was. My father. 'Cos I wasn't born then.
 And - anyway she - gets she gets out of that place, she comes up to London, my mother with the three child you see, 'course this is what my mother tells me.
