oor and said that your Robert or Andrew had hit so and so she'd go out and bring - bring them all in. She wouldn't row with them or anything else but she'd want to know why it was, you know, but - not - she wouldn't row over children. As I said before, sh
e
 had that very - bad experience when she was in Liverpool about these two men - the one fought with the other over the children and said she'd never quarrel over children. That she just - bring them in and chastise them, you see, and then they'd have to t
ake their - boots off and clean them or go out in the yard and play for a little while.
