No. I - I had to left - I left when I was - well, nearly sixty you see, up to six - six months before I was sixty. I had to leave you see. 
It was only through falling off the bus. See. Oh yes, yes. I would have - well, I mean, they wouldn't have given me the sack because - not that I say it, but I was such a good worker and they - and they always had everything ready for them to - do the cha
nnels you see for the fluorescent lighting, I used to do the wiring and the holder and cut and trim 'em and put them in different holders you see for them and - yes, it ;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 What was your life at home like after you left school?
