\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Your mother you told her was a Catholic and you were brought up a Catholic?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Yes. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 What about your father, any idea what his religion was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Well he - no, but he turned Catholic
 when he - on - like when he was ill you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 But before that he hadn't been a Catholic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
No, he was a Scotsman dad was, I don't really know what he - his religion was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 He didn't have a religion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Not really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 It was from your mother that the religious side came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
That St Margarets Church you mentioned, I wondered if it was the one along that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Yes, that is it, yes, yes. By Canning Town, yes. Yes. Yes. We came - we were all christened there, baptised, like us - the last five was all baptised there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 That was a lovely description you gave of all the altars outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Oh yes, we had the - we had the outdoor processions. It was very nice.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 It must have been lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Oh 
it was beautiful. See we didn't have any cameras because we could have taken some photos and showed you you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 I wonder if they still have that, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Not now. No, I think it's been stopped because - I think it's to do with the traffic - rules or something like that, I think that's been stopped you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
It would have made it difficult because we forget how the traffic has changed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
That's right, yes, really you do, yes, but - well the Canon that - used to come round in the outd
oor procession, he came in and see me the other evening. Yes. 'Cos I was in - queer in bed, see. He's eighty now, he said oh - 'cos he - well I've known him about fifty years now. And I'm seventy-six myself. Yes. Seventy-six last May. 28}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\super\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318  of May.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 So he's known you for many years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Yes, many years, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Did he take an interest in the children when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Oh very - yes, he did do. 'Cos they used to go to school there you see. And then the latter part when - when I could - mothe
r got a pram and then she - they used to take me to church - to school in a pram you see, and then a - him - a chap - one of the men used to start - used to carry me in and - in the classroom and put me right up by the back in the classroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 I remember you said they didn't let you go out at playtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Oh well I couldn't you see, I couldn't walk then you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 But even after, when you were nine, you were able to walk a bit weren't you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Well - when - when I was nine and I first had my 
ankle - my knee done then I could stand 'cos they - surgical instruments and crutches then you see, that's the only way I could stand then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Would they let you out in the playground then or did they think it wasn't safe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Oh - well - no I used to 
sit in the classroom because teacher wouldn't let me go out because it was a bit rough you know and I might have got knocked down or something like that, so otherwise I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 So you'd stay in the classroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Yes, I'd sit in the classroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 By yourself or did she sit with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Oh no, she'd sit with you and have a bit of lunch or, you know, that. So - no, I - I didn't go to school very long, I don't think I went to school about eleven - six months altogether because I - excuse me - in and out 
of hospital all the time you see. So I couldn't very well - go to school much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
But that sounded a lovely place in Gloucester where you went for convalescence.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Oh yes, it was beautiful convalescent home, yes. There was only about - I think only 
about five of us there you see, and that lady - I was there in - nearly a year and five months in Gloucestershire. 'Cos the lady wanted to adopt me but mother said no. I'd been away too long from home, she wanted me home. But - I regret it myself because 
I think I'd have had a - good education you see and all that up there some - to fall back on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 She took a great interest in you did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
She did. And they - they all did. He used to give us little lessons in the - you know, in the morning and - I was very fond of the piano and she was going - she would have learnt me how to play - had me learnt how to play the piano and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 That would have been nice wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 It was lucky you had that chance to recuperate in the country wasn't it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Oh - yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Was it her home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Yes, it was the - one of the - one of the - it was rather a big house you see and this lady opened it for convalescent people see. I suppose there was three or four - all convalescent from hospital you see where -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 So it was her own home, she wasn't employed to nurse there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 No dear, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 She was a lady who wanted to do good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
To do good, that's right, yes. Yes. It was really her brother's house and it run by her an
d her brother you see but - he never used to come there, had his own house but - it was run by the two of them you see. And - it was - ooh it was a lovely little place there, quite nice you know. Had a lovely garden, and they used to take us out in little
 trap and pony, you see, it was quite nice, it was really lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Did you like the countryside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 I do, I love country really. I think it's very very nice.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Was that right in Gloucester?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Where's Morton-in-the-Marsh- in Morton-in-Marsh. Gloucestershire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 That must have been very nice
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Your Uncle Tom and Uncle Jim?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Oh I don't remember much about them, they're all dead and buried now. All of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 You didn't see a lot of them when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 No, not very much. No, not very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Your mother was more or less on her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Oh - mostly, yes, yes. Always on her own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Did your father have any relations in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 No, he was an only child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Did his parents stay in Scotland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 I d
on't know, my - I don't know anything about his parents. All I know that - he ran way from home, and - he - he was a bad man I suppose, I don't know, but he ran away from home and went to sea and - 'course - I don't know how mother got in contact with him
, somewhere in Liverpool, I don't really know. You see. So - I mean even when she was young you see she had to look after three of them. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 When she first met him -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
I don't really know, I couldn't say dear. 'Cos I don't know anything about the 
- much, see mum never told me a lot about what happened, or the - said that she was left when she was ten, and these three - the young boy was only eighteen months old when her mother died. 'Cos her mother was only thirty-seven years of old then when she 
died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 So she had to work very hard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Yes, well you see - she had to look after those children, well - her father was a glassblower I believe, I don't know, and - when there was no work they used to tour the country, going to different - you know, 
places where the glassblowers was working, and make collections, and them that was out of work they used to share the money between them you see. So I mean she's always had a hard life really. 'Til she married - my step-father, then it wasn't too bad you 
know, it was very - she had rather a more easier and - didn't have to worry much about - money or meals or anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 That was lucky wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Because he was a shipwright you see, and - he'd done his - his seven years apprentice - ship and then of course he came over here to - to London in the ship and that's how my father knew him you see. And that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Did your father give up going to sea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Well he had to, yes, he had to, he couldn't do nothing. He had a very severe - severe accident he had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 But that accident was during a spell on land was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Yes, while he was on ships - doing work on the ships see, he fell down the ships hold going past the - something over the deck - the plate was up or something and he fel
l down and it was dark and he couldn't see, and of course he was in hospital very very ill. 'Course sort of everything was, you know - underneath sort of with \{BLANK\}
 you see. 'Cos he was given up in - Greenwich hospital you see. But anyway he came - he got over that you see. But he never worked after that. No. You see, them days you couldn't get help like you can today. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 He wasn't a docker or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
No, he wasn't a docker. He - he was a - what did they call it now - oh can't think of the name of it. He was on - on the ship you see. On the wench end, he was on the wench end, what they call the wench end, I don't know what that means but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 But he'd be away at sea a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 No. After - he worked ashore after he got married you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 He gave up going away to be with your mother did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Yes, he used to work -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 I got a bit muddled between the two of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Yes, that's right, yes. My step-father, he went away to sea. Then when he got married he didn't go away to sea, he just worked ashore. See on the ships - the boats ashore. He used to work for Harland and Wolfe, see, in that - when he was here.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Silvertown?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Yes, that's right. Used to work Harland and Wolfe's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 It was very interesting, a lady and 
gentleman who live near me, I interviewed them you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 And they mentioned that Peggy Dooley that you mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Very many people around that area knew him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 They actually knew him, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 They lived in Crescent Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Oh yes, that's not far from where I lived in Butcher's Road. Off Butchers Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 And they mentioned Peggy Dooley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Oh well, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 So much a character he was that many people remembered him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Yes, oh - he was 
an awful character really. Used to take his artificial off - leg off and he'd plague the policemen like anything you know. You'd often see him being brought along on the stretcher to the station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 And your mother used to tell you about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Yes.
 She did. Yes. Well I maybe used to see him because - when mum was ill she was in the - sit in the front room and I'd go in to her after I'd done what I had to do, and - all of a sudden you'd see the policemen and the - and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10777455\charrsid2754318 stretch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318  her coming along. Mu
m said, well there's Peggy Dooley again, she'd say you know, so funny to see it. But - he was a real terror when he had drink in him, he's - that - that's what used to cause all the trouble you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Were there a lot of people drinking round there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Oh I suppose there was, I don't really know those people. But anyway, used to bring him along on this, so funny. And of course the children would run behind him you know. Make fun of him and all that. But - he only used to get a little fine I think, I 
don't really know what - happened to him after that. Or if they took him for his own good you see. In case anything else happened to him, but he was a real - he was a real character.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Do you remember people doing knees up Mother Brown or dancing in the street?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Oh used to have organs outside the door and they - these chaps used to dress up as men - women, you know, and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Do funny turns would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 They - they - in - in the road you know, they'd go rou
nd collecting and all that you see, 'course that's all - it was the - time of - no work you see or anything and they were glad to do that, they all - they'd have the organ for a day or so and then they'd go round the streets and - and that's what they'd d
o you see. To get money. You see, the - very sad really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
I remember the story you told Mrs English about your mother giving money to the poor beggar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Oh yes, that was - that was - you see that - I can always remember her sitting in the room becau
se she - you know, she see this poor old chap come along and big tears rolling down her cheeks, you know, when she this see this poor old chap come along. So she said, is there any soup in that. I said, yes there's a little mum. Hot it up, she said, and b
ring the - the old gentleman in, she said, and - put him on the stairs and give him this soup I'd hotted up and - she had in her purse was a ha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10777455\charrsid2754318 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 penny. And she said, here you are, give him this ha'penny, she said, and - and - that's all I've got, she said, a
nd - I - anyway oh he blessed her and thanked her you know, like the old people do and that, and that you see. It didn't matter who it was - it didn't matter what she had - the last she had she'd give you - give it to the people you know, to help them, 'c
os she said - she knew what it was to be hard up. Well we was hard up then really but - of course the - that was her heart you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 She was always for other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Yes, she always said, never mind Mary, she said, you'll never want for a friend 
if anything happens to me. And it's true, I've had very good friends you know. Especially since I came here. And since I was ill I've got very good neighbours to come in to me. Very very good neighbours, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Did your mother have very good neighbours
 when you were young do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Well she never mixed with neighbours you see, mother never mixed with anybody. And she always believed in - if you - doesn't matter how hard up you were so long as you paid your rent, people out - and your door s
hut people outside would never know what you had inside. She always believed in that. And she worked hard to get the rent so she - at least you've got a roof over your head, she said, and shut - shut your door and nobody knows anything else what's in ther
e. Well that was true and all you see. No, she never mixed with people. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Would she help them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
She'd help them if they want - if they wanted help they'd only have to come to mother and ask if she'd help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 And they would come would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
If they wanted help she'd come, if they were sick or ill she could - go and nurse them and that you see, clean their place up. But of course she couldn't help them financially or anything, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 There's a lot of sort of help you can give to people other ways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 But it's definite -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Like giving them a hand with their home if their not well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Oh yes. Yes. Because in Liverpool as our mother said, if a neighbour missed another neighbour for two days they go and knock on the door.
 Well see the door was always - open, they'd lift up the latch and they'd go in, you see, and see if that person was ill. Well then they'd turn to and if the children were - at school they'd - get a meal ready and give it to the children, and do the place
 out and have it clean for the husband if he come home from work you see or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 But she didn't find that when she came to London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Not the same, no. No, they're different people altogether, London people then. That's what she couldn't understand you see. If a person was ill nobody would know because nobody ever go in to the person. Not in London. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 But your older sister used to help her did she, if your mother wasn't well?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Oh she'd come along I expect when she wasn't 
very well you see. Because - you see, I I was the last one to be born so I don't really remember quite a lot - about things see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Did the priest call round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Oh yes, the priest and the nuns and that, they always called round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Did they help with clothing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Well - mother would never ask you see. She would never - if - if they would they sometimes - if they have anything but - she - if you had any money it was - of her own she'd go down to the - corner of the street and there was a l
ady - lot of people sit there with - clothes and rags and - second clothes and that, if there's anything there she could - get, she'd get it you see. And make up for us. Bring it home and wash it and make it up for us you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 But you don't remember people giving her things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Oh no. No. No. The only people that she went to was the - the R.O. and they were very unkind. Very unkind. Oh they were really cruel to people. You daren't have a mat on the floor - 'cos we only had orange boxes and - f
or tables and chairs you see, with - with covers on them they were just as well you know. And that - but - but of course mum had one or two - gentlemen friends that knew mother you see, knew her all her life how hard she had to work and that, see, then th
e
y spoke up for her. But then you only got two - loaves and - a - three shillings. Nothing for your rent. Nothing at all. She had to go out and work to pay the rent you know, and that. But that's one thing she did believe in, paying the rent. Whatever else
 
you went without she said, because you can eat and sleep which - in the street but you cannot sleep in it. She believed in all that she said. She was very - very - I remember her telling me one Sunday that - we never had anything - only some gravy and pot
a
toes for dinner, and - of course she used to go over to - some friends at Stratford, and she went over there one day and the boys went out in the street and - children playing those days, oh she said, we've had not dinner. We've only had gravy and potatoe
s, we've not had no meat. My mother was so annoyed about that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 She didn't think they should say that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
No, not really, no. No. 'Cos they didn't have any meat they never had no dinner. It was so funny that was you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Do you ever remember the school offering any meals, free meals or so on?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
No. Not when we went to school. No. 'Cos they weren't - it wasn't invented then when we went to school. Whatever - mother could get we used to go home and have it - if it was only Oxo and som
ething like that you know and bread - used to go home every dinner time and have something hot what she could get you see. Find. Yes. Still there you are, it's just one of those things you see. But anyway she was a real forager, was - my mother was. She u
s
ed to go out and - pick up - bit of rags in the street, bring 'em home and wash 'em and take 'em to the rag shop, to get soap and stuff to wash our clothes - so as we'd go to school clean the next morning. So - one thing she - she did keep us clean, that'
s one thing she did do. Yes, see she never - let us go to school dirty or anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Did she talk quite a lot about her young days, you seem to know quite a lot about her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Well - sometimes she - she'd sit and talk about it and other tim
es she wouldn't, you know. There's quite a lot of things I should have known but I don't know you see. There's quite a lot of things I should have know but I didn't - know. And of course me being with mum never - I never realized that - true she was eight
y-one when she died but I mean I couldn't realize that - it would be important to know all these things you see until after she was gone. Well I - I couldn't read the mind of things that I should know you see, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 But she told you quite a bit about her childhood didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Oh yes. Oh yes, she really did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Do you ever remember anybody turning against somebody in your street or in the neighbourhood for anything and making a big noise outside their house with kettles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 No. If - if 
there was anything like that - children would be fighting one against the other, she'd bring them in - and close the door. She wouldn't let them be out you see and then - if it - she - somebody might come knocking at the door saying, your Johnnie's done s
o
 and so. Well she'd bring him in. And - make him undress and clean the boots or something, then she's say, you can play out in the garden - the yard for an hour, she said, and you're not going out there any more. She wouldn't make any - disturbance or any
t
hing like that you see with children because she told me once when she was in Liverpool there was two children playing outside, and one child hit the other a bit hard and he went in crying to his - up to his mum. His dad was there, I suppose it was on a S
u
nday, he just have had one or two drinks and of course the other - man, he brought the other man out, they started fighting and this man hit him and the other man fell and hit his head - head on the kerb. Of course the poor man died you see. Now that man 
w
as in his coffin, his children was outside playing. See that was in Liverpool, so mum said, I would never - she said, I would never quarrel over children, that sort of - woke her up you know to the fact that - it's not worth - quarrelling over children, j
ust bring them in and chastise them. This is not argue - not arguing with people outside. So that's how she always brought us up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 And did she tell you that if another child hit you you should hit back?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 No, she never - she never had that nature at all. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 She didn't think people should hit back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 You mentioned she'd have a little cat-o'nine tails?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Oh that was - that was when - we was all home for dinner you know or that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Did she ever actually use it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 I don't think - no, she never, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 It was just a threat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
That's right. That's so because you see my brothers wouldn't eat carrots or anything like that, if she made him they put 'em on - the other brother's plate you see and - and she would
n't allow talking at meals. She never liked you talking at meals. So that's why she used to put it on the table. Never used it or anything like that. So anyway she - it was only just to frighten you, see, to eat your - food up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Would she give you a scolding then if you did anything wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Oh she'd give - shed give you a good scolding, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 But not hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Oh no, she wouldn't hit us, no. No. And yet I was never spoilt, thank God, I do - I am grateful for - for - for that because - I don't know how I should have managed to look after the home after I lost the - see but anyway I'm grateful I wasn't spoiled.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 That's a terrible thing for a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Oh it is. Yes. Yes. Specially in my condition you know. Disabled and all that. Sti
ll I looked after her all right and - she never had - she wouldn't let nobody else do anything for her, only me. No, no, no. When my sister come in to do anything she said, no. Mary'll do it, she could - she knows how to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Were you her favourite when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 No I don't think -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Do you remember very poor elderly people when you were a child being around?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Well I - I can't really because - see I was always indoors wasn't I. See. When I was about - and mother wouldn't - in a
ny case I couldn't walk out, I used to crawl on my hands and knees, you see, and I didn't stand until I was nine years of age. You see, well I couldn't go out very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 So every where you went before that age she had to carry you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Yes, I had to be carried.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Were you quite light and small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Well I wasn't very big, I was only - wasn't very big anyway, I wasn't - not heavy - child to carry. You know, she'd long black curls down all round - but - anyway, I wasn't really - I think from the a
ge of - from the age of about twelve, I - after I got out of hospital and that I started doing the housework and all that, you know, keeping the place clean for mum and helping her in that way. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 You must have been a great help to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Well i
t was really because - she couldn't do a lot with her bronchitis and her heart trouble you see then, she had it for quite a few years. But then it was the 'flu - influenza took her off because I - I had it, and she - she - she had a very bad attack of bro
n
chitis, so then like she was up and down, then I took the - influenza on the Wed - on a Friday evening, see, and she tried to help me. Well then of course here being weak she caught it you see. Yes, that was in January. She lay a whole week - dying, she h
ad a very heart attack, and I looked after her all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 So she was in her own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Pardon. Oh yes, she was at home, and I'm grateful really she was, that I was able to do what I did for her. Yes. Because it'll - even no you see there's a lo
t of - poor souls away and they're not able to help themselves in hospital, and they're left there, they can't - cant help themselves with their food you see, it's taken away and they're sort of - they sort of die with - with hunger don't they. Really in 
h
ospitals some of them do, because if they're paralysed and they can't help theirselves, lift their hands up to feed themselves and the nurses come back, they take their dinner away from them, they don't stop to give it to them. That I know is the truth be
c
ause - because - one or two - ladies that their husbands and that have been there you see, and they used to have to go in the dinner time and feed their husbands. See? Well I mean if you get old they don't need to treat you like that need they really. I m
ean it's awful I think, myself. Very bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 I think some of the nurses are kind though aren't they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
Some are but there are so many of these - dark nurses that they're not - haven't got you know they haven't sort of got much - a lot of patience wit
h our people really I don't think. Some of 'em are not - really. But - of course - I suppose they've got their feelings - about - 'cos it - not many people like British people is there, not really, at all. I mean these other countries, they're just - it's
 
just a matter of - of course I mean although they shake hands and smile but they hate British under their heart, in their hearts they don't like Britain at all. They never have and I suppose because - when they read back the history of what our people use
d
 to do years ago to the - black people abroad it - and I think they're very very bad indeed to the blacks. Real - real cruel they were to them. 'Cos after all they're all God's creatures and they're all human beings aren't they. I mean, they under - they 
d
o - they've got their feelings the same as everybody else. Well I think it's disgraceful for countries to see all this starvation. I think - oh - vile, absolutely vile. Shocking. They're afraid to go without anything themselves they are. They won't make a
 
sacrifice to - help these kind of people. Now this Mrs Ghandi she could do quite a lot, she's a wealthy person and yet she's come over here for more help. Why not let them - Mrs Gandhi - she's come over here for more help. Well why doesn't she - she - giv
e a few thousand up what they've got - but they won't will they. She is a wealthy person I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
I suppose in a place like India if she gave up all her wealth it would be like a drop in the ocean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 Oh well yes I know that would be - but it would b
e an example wouldn't it to show them and that. She would be quite a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7222989 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 They have got terrible problems there haven't they?
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid7222989 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2715041 MH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12131203\charrsid2754318 
They have. Every - I think all countries are upside down now aren't they really. There's not one - not one country that's 
at peace I don't think all - in the world now much. Not now. No. And they've got more now than they ever had, I mean they're not left - they've got enough to eat.
\par }}